text.tspan: Tau² calculated by DerSimonian and Laird method.

Sample sizes adjusted for clustering using an ICC of 0.02 (author’s do not mention any assumptions for ICC. An ICC of 0.02 is usually used for school-based interventions). Design effect applied to account for 2 classes (clusters).
(C) Blinding of participants and personnel (performance bias): iron deficiency/anaemia; Hb; iron status/deficiency

(E) Incomplete outcome data (attrition bias): iron deficiency/anaemia; Hb; iron status/deficiency
